comment:
This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head
I'm here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life
Then as now fly
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry and then die
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we're not dead
No, we're not dead
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you
From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you

comment:
JINJER
Vivace (Perennial)

[Intro]
Cet automne ressemble plutôt à des funérailles, à mon sens
La plus longue chanson de deuil
Et non pour ce qui n’est plus
Mais pour ce qui doit durer

[Verse 1]
La nature épuisée est si tragique et suicidaire
Oh combien spectaculaire est-elle lorsqu’elle se tue
Les racines de la mort rampent lentement vers ses orteils
Au moment où la dernière feuille tombe de sa tête
Je suis là, avec elle, dévêtue
Avec quelques pétales sur ma poitrine
Nous avons partagé des opiacés et laissé les paysages faire de même
J’aime ta chaleur, mais je préfère néanmoins dormir au froid, seule
Nous avons fixé nos yeux vers le ciel
Pour voir une volée nous faire ses adieux

[Chorus]
Au revoir
Souhaitons que nous nous reverrons la prochaine fois
Alors, s’il te plaît, reviens célébrer ce festival de la vie
Mais pour l’instant, envole-toi
Aujourd’hui, tu as atteint le point de non-retour
Maintenant, pleure et ensuite meurs
Demain, je te retrouverai avec tes cellules restaurées

[Bridge]
Tradition annuelle de destruction de masse
Au nom de la reconstruction totale
Ma plus grande source de confusion
La raison de toute décadence et désillusion
Sous une glace permanente
Nous avons trouvé un paradis à couper le souffle
Non, nous ne sommes pas mortes
Non, nous ne sommes pas mortes
Nous profitons seulement de ce coma

[Outro]
Des cendres de mes racines
La nouvelle moi s’élèvera pour vivre à nouveau
Ceci est poésie de la jeunesse
Ceci est poésie de moi et de toi
Des cendres de mes racines
La nouvelle moi s’élèvera pour vivre à nouveau
Ceci est poésie de la jeunesse
Ceci est poésie de moi et de toi
Traduit par
Marc Ouellet
author: Marc Ouellet

comment:
This song is a total masterpiece. I dare to say it's as beautiful as a Nothing Else Matters by Metallica or a Down in a Whole by Alice in Chains. Everything is so on point, so well put together. The lyrics/vocals, the instrumentals... everything sounds so good and "makes sense". I confess I didn't even think that kind of good music was still being made nowadays. 

Thanks, Jinjer, for restoring my faith in today's music.

comment: I'm no metalhead but I love Jinjer. Listening to them is the definition of cognitive dissonance: holding 2 seemingly opposing ideas at the same time that should contradict each other and yet, they work beautifully. Here, it's the juxtaposition of the sweet lyrics: [ Goodbye! / May we see each other next time/ So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life! ]. It's growled at me by a demonic voice and I cannot explain with I find this delightful. And not only are the lyrics dope but the music is on point and masterfully crafted. I love having my brain scrambled by them with every song. It's quite a discovery and I can feel/experience the beauty of it.

comment:
I grew up in the 80s, listening to things before my time. Ozzy, Dio, Jimi, The Animals, Johnny Cash, Abba, The Bee Gees. Def Leppard. krokus and my favorite Iron Maiden. Years gone by, Techno, Slayer, Anthrax, Metallica, Megadeth. I never thought I'd find more great music. SOD, Pantera, Limp Bizcut, Staind, Papa Roach, incubus, Third Eye Blind, MIS  System of a Down, Lamb of God,
Grew somber, Fiona Apple, Tori Amos, Yeah, Yeah Yeahs. White Stripes, Chevelle. Peter Gabriel.
Then I heard the Blue Ep from Oceans of Slumber. Vk goes wild and The incredible band called Now Now. Butcher Babies somehow led to Jinjer and here I am. I've been lucky to hear the greatest music in the world. In a short life. Jinjer has been since that piceses vid, that first time she screamed. The most incredible thing I have ever heard. Just wanted to say that to the world.
Thank you.

comment:
I was born with music in my soul, I have listened almost to every genre that every country has to offer and I liked metal most of them all. Linkin Park as a Nu-metal became my most favorite band of all time listening to them for almost a decade now. I've been listening to a lot of metal genres and vocalists seems to sound like each other, almost every one except the real ones, I found JINJER a year ago through my musician friend and the moment I saw her scream and roar while watching PISCES' studio version I was incredibly astonished.
I felt like I was a baby while listening and I was ashamed of myself, After a year of listening to her I learnt how to Metal Scream with high pitches, I never knew I could do it until I got ashamed of myself lol. She is truly one of a kind.

Y no lo hagas descansar hasta que hable conmigo, que así sea!. Por los poderes de la tierra, por la presencia del fuego, por la inspiración del aire por las virtudes del agua invoco a las 13 almas benditas, por la fuerza de los corazones sangrados y de las lágrimas derramadas por amor y que se dirija en donde esté en este momento (...) Y traiga su espirita te mi amarrandolo definitivamente al mío (...) Que su espíritu se bañe de la escencia de mi amor y me lo devuelva cuadruplicado. Que (...) Jamás desee a otra persona y que tenga ojos solo para mí y que así sea.! Salve Pomba Gira María Padilha Reina de las siete encrucijadas yo te ruego así: ahora Gira ven mujer gira a mi favor trayendo a (...) Para mí. Pidiendo así mismo: aire mueve, fuego transforma, agua firma, tierra cura y la rueda va girando , va girando y la rueda va girando trae Pomba Gira María Padilha a (...) De vuelta a mi lo más rápido posible, que no quiera a otra persona y que se sienta bien solamente a mi lado (...) Que (...) Sienta que me extraña que venga a verme y que me pida que nunca lo a abandoné. Que (...) (...) Seamos uno solo (...) Que así sea, así sea y así está hecho. Salve Pomba Gira, salve siete ayas, salve sus hermanas María mulamba , María Padilha y todas las otras de la falange. Salve siete sayas mi buena amiga mujer de las siete encrucijadas de las mujeres y de los hombres. Salve siete sayas mi buena y gloriosa princesa conozco tu fuerza y tú poder, te pido que atiendas mi siguiente deseo: Que (...) No descanse hasta que estemos juntos. Que el cuerpo de (...) Deseé por mi (...) Que no vea a otras mujeres y que no consiga verlas como mujeres. Que ninguna mujer consiga hacer sentir a (...) Deseo o placer, solamente yo (...) Tengo ese poder dado por ti mi reina. Que (...) Me ame, me bese, me abracé y me lleve en su corazón solamente a mi (...) También que (...) Quiera estar a todo instante ahora y siempre a mi lado . Que (...) Tenga mi imagen en sus pensamientos en todos los momentos de sus días. Que ahora con quién esté y en donde esté(...) Piense en mi antes de dormir, que tenga sueños conmigo y al despertarse que piense en mi haciendo que cada día me ame más y más. Si está durmiendo que se despierte con anheló y sienta placer por mi. Que solamente escuchando mi voz (...) Sienta un deseo fuera de lo normal por mi como nunca sintió por nadie y que nunca sentirá por nadie más. Salve siete sayas. Mi buena y gloriosa princesa por las siete sayas que acompañan sus pasos ruego y suplico que amarres a (...) En sus siete sayas y en sus siete guizos de su ropa para mí (...) Agradezco por estar trabajando a mi favor , voy a divulgar su nombre a cambio de esta petición de traer a (...) Siempre conmigo para que sea solo mío y se aleje de todas las otras mujeres para siempre. Que piense siempre en mi, que quiera estar conmigo, que regrese a mí y no pueda vivir sin mi (...) Pues tendrá miedo de perderme y que venga diciendo que me quiere junto a él por siempre. Que así sea, así será y así está hecho. Confío en las falanges del Pomba Gira Reina de las siete encrucijadas. Cada vez que lea está oración ella más fuerte se hará por eso voy a difundir esta oración a las siete esquinas del mundo pidiendo a la madre que me conceda este deseo de estar con (...) Que los espíritus de las falanges de Pomba estén soplando en los oídos de (...) Mi nombre (...) Día y noche diciéndole que me hable, que me busqué y venga a mi. El aquí un poco más no va a poder comer ni dormir ni hacer cualquier cosa hasta que esté conmigo. Confío en el poder de las siete encrucijadas y voy a continuar divulgando está oración poderosa. Sin embargo no se puede volver atrás, debido a que si se pidió amarrar, amarrara. Jamás dejará de correr detrás de usted. Con fue y divulgue. Que así sea, así será y así está hecho. Amén. Publica está oración cuatro veces. Cuando termines escribirás en la planta del pie izquierdo el nombre de la persona amada Después pisa fuerte con el pie y diga: ( Nombre de la persona amada) 3x debajo de mi pie 3x te tengo 3x te amarro 3x te mantengo Por los poderes de las trece almas benditas. El sueño que tengas esa noche no lo debes revelar a nadie..

comment:
Perennial Lyrics

This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal!
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself!
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head

I'm here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye!
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life!

Then as now fly!
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry! And then die!
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we're not dead
No, we're not dead
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you!

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you!

comment: No one knows what the song truly means to the band. All I take from it is a story of life/death/rebirth.  The circle of life. And that is what I will take from it. You can make anything political, but by doing so you are diluting the true essence of a thing. Remember, the earth will rotate. Seasons will come and go, as they have for millions of years before "sentient" man existed. And will continue to do so long after "sentient" man is gone away. Do we really want to waste the little time we have here arguing about a flawed process we invented? I will not.

comment:
Traducción a Español

"Perennial"

Este otoño me parece un funeral.
La canción más larga de pena.
Y no por lo que ha pasado.
Si no por lo que durará.


¡La naturaleza agotada es tan trágica y suicida!
¡Oh, qué espectacular es cuando se mata ella misma!
La agonía se arrastra lentamente a los dedos de sus pies
A medida que la última hoja se cae de su cabeza.


Estoy aquí con ella sin vestir.
Con unos pocos pétalos en mis senos.
Compartimos opiáceos y dejamos que los paisajes hagan lo mismo.
Me encanta tu calor, pero aun prefiero dormir sola en el frío.
Fijamos nuestros ojos hacia el cielo.
Para ver que un vuelo nos despida.


¡Adiós!
Ojalá nos veamos la próxima vez.
Así que por favor, ¡vuelve para celebrar este festival de la vida!


Entonces como ahora vuela!
Hoy has llegado al punto sin retorno.
Ahora llora ¡Y luego muere!
Mañana me reuniré contigo con tus células restauradas.


Tradición anual de destrucción masiva.
En nombre de la reconstrucción total.
Mi mayor fuente de confusión.
La razón de la decadencia y la desilusión.
Bajo hielo permanente encontramos un paraíso que deja sin aliento.
No, no estamos muertos,
No, no estamos muertos,
Solo disfrutando de coma


De las cenizas de mis raíces, la nueva yo se levantará para vivir otra vez.
Esto es poesía de juventud, esto es poesía de mí y de ti.

comment:
This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head
I´m here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life
Then as now fly
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry and then die
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we´re not dead
No, we´re not dead
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you
From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you

comment:
LYRICS:
This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head
I'm here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life
Then as now fly
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry and then die
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we're not dead
No, we're not dead
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you
From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth
This is poetry of me and you

comment: Now bear in mind that all  band members have family members living in the occupied eastern part of Ukraine. Jinjer had a courage to continue doing what they love despite living in a poor, unstable country where metal music cannot make you money for living. Over the years their dedication made them recognizable on the Ukrainian heavy scene and now they are rocking all over the world with their truly unique music. I feel like they are breathing in new life into Napalm Records and metal music itself. This is fucking remarkable.

comment:
Стал фанатом Jinjer после того, как увидел Pisces. Я ищу в ваших песнях чего-то похожего - и в этой немного нахожу. Я здесь, пожалуй, ради 3 вещей:
1. Спокойная партия, мелодия, звучание, приятное слуху. 2.Сильная агрессивная партия, максимально контрастирующая со спокойной. 3. Кульминация (Pisces - 4:25)
Я здесь не ради чего-то похожего на Sit Stay Roll Over. Если я буду искать что-то такое, я пожалуй, предпочту Emmure или Heart Of A Coward.
У них есть то, чего нет у Тани - мощнейший, плотнейший !мужской! гроул (У Тани он тоже очень мощный и плотный, но всё равно не мужской).
Зато у вас есть то, чего нет у них - контраст между экстримом и нежным и сильным чистым голосом.
Не понимаю, зачем бороться с титанами на их же поле - когда в вашей власти открыть свою собственную, никем до этого не изведанную, территорию.
Желаю вам успехов.

comment:
Соглашусь со многими: это ваша лучшая песня на данный момент. По крайней мере среди тех, на которые есть видео. Очень нравятся такие тенденции в вашей музыке: больше дэт, чем прогрессив, и при этом мелодик... Есть и жескач, который качает, и одновременно ласкающая слух мелодичность - это двойной удар, просто дабл килл!.. Пожалуйста, делайте больше музыки в таком ключе!
В вокале, как мне показалось, тоже появились изменения, если говорить про чистый: больше планов и нюансов, оттенков и переливов... Ещё красивее, ещё нежнее и проникновеннее, чем прежде...
И всему этому способствует лирика, которая отлично написана, глубокая и погружающая в атмосферу произведения наравне с видео...
Клип заслуживает отдельных слов: насыщенные, выпуклые образы, за которыми из глубины прошедших столетий самим собой тянется шлейф из легенд и мистических историй... Он заставляет разгорячёно работать воображение и самостоятельно дополнять, додумывать повествование, в центре которого его Героиня, в бесконечной череде смертей и воскрешений отождествляемая с Природой, и, то блистающая в своей ослепительной красоте и кружащая в земном водовороте жизней, то увядающая, как поздняя осенняя листва, и стоящая на пороге своей могилы...
И когда это всё соединяется с музыкой, текстом и голосом... Получается очень символично, очень величественно и красиво, брутально, грязно и возвышено одновременно - потрясающая смесь, тянущая на самое изысканное колдовское зелье, которое когда-либо варила украинская группа в истории...

P.S. Особенно мне понравилось, что они здесь используют более стандартную структуру песни. В отличие от "I Speak Astronomy", например, 1-ая и 2-ая части которой воспринимаются как 2 отдельные песни, просто соединённые вместе, что мешает моему личному восприятию композиции... А могла бы быть потрясающая работа... Но в существующем виде "I Speak Astronomy" воспринимается как демо - незаконченная версия произведения. Или даже сразу 2 демо, записанные в виде какго-то короткого мегамикса... В общем, что-то сырое, какая-то недоделка...

comment: Maybe my favorite Jinjer song so far. I love the philosophical theme of death/rebirth, and what seems to be the reference to Yule. Jinjer's lyrics are always really sophisticated, but the meaning of other songs has usually been quite straightforward. This one seems more complex. I can't tell if it is talking about a relationship using the symbolism of Yule as a metaphor, or talking about being connected to nature using the symbolism of romance as a metaphor. comment:
This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last
Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal!
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself!
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head
I´m here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye!

May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life!
Then as now fly!
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry! And then die!
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we´re not dead,
No, we´re not dead,
Just enjoying coma
From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth,
This is poetry of me and you!
From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth,
This is poetry of me and you!

comment:
LYRICS (may be some wrong lol):

This autumn feels like funeral to me
the longest song of grief
and not for what has passed
but for what shall last

Exhausted nature is tragic and suicidal!
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself!
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
as the last leaf is falling off her head
I´m here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscaped do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in a cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye!
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life!

Then as now fly!
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry! And then die!
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion 
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice we found breathless paradise
No, we´re not dead
No, we´re not dead
just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots the new me will rise to live again

comment:
Lyrics:

This autumn feels like funeral to me
The longest song of grief.
And not for what has passed
But for what shall last.

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal!
Oh how spectacular she is  when she kills herself!
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head.

I´m here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone.
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye!
May we see each other next time.
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life!

Then as now fly!
Today you reached the point of no return.
Now cry! And then die!
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored.

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction.
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion.
Under permanent ice we found a breathless paradise 
No, we´re not dead,
No, we´re not dead,
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots the new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth, this is poetry of me and you!

comment:
This autumn feels like funeral to me.
The longes song of grief.
And not for what has passed,
But for what I shall last.

Exhausted nature is so tragic and suicidal!
Oh how spectacular she is when she kills herself!
Death throes are slowly crawling to her toes
As the last leaf is falling off her head

I´m here with her undressed
With a few petals on my breasts
We shared opiates and let the landscapes do the same
I love your warmth but yet prefer to sleep in cold alone
We fixed our eyes up to the sky
To see a flight send us farewell

Goodbye!
May we see each other next time
So please, come back to celebrate this festival of life!
Then as now fly!
Today you reached the point of no return
Now cry! And then die!
Tomorrow I will meet you with your cells restored

Annual tradition of mass destruction
In the name of total reconstruction
My biggest source of confusion
The reason of decay and disillusion
Under permanent ice
We found a breathless paradise
No, we´re not dead,
No, we´re not dead,
Just enjoying coma

From the ashes of my roots
The new me will rise to live again
This is poetry of youth,
This is poetry of me and you!﻿
